# ============================================================================
# TESTING MANAGEMENT NOTES
# ============================================================================

# TEST OUTPUTS:
# - Test outputs are generated during test execution
# - Coverage reports show code coverage but can be regenerated
# - Test reports provide execution details but are temporary

# SNAPSHOT TESTING:
# - Snapshot files capture expected output for comparison
# - These should typically be committed for regression testing
# - Consider whether to include or exclude based on project needs

# PERFORMANCE TESTING:
# - Performance test results vary between runs and environments
# - Benchmark results are useful for comparison but can be regenerated
# - Load test outputs are large and temporary

# SECURITY SCANNING:
# - Security scan results may contain sensitive vulnerability information
# - Quality tool outputs help identify issues but can be regenerated
# - Consider excluding scan results from version control

# BEST PRACTICES:
# - Store test expectations (snapshots, fixtures) in version control
# - Exclude generated test outputs and reports
# - Use CI/CD systems to generate and archive test artifacts

# ============================================================================
# END OF TESTING PATTERNS
# ============================================================================

